**Description of the problem including expected versus actual behavior**:

Removing the rollover action while an index is in the `check-rollover-ready` step will cause it to get stuck in the hot phase without error in ILM explain. This behavior may or may not be by design, or something ILM was not meant to do, so expected behavior could vary:

1. Allow the hot phase to complete to prevent further writes to the index and move to the next desired phase. Or,
2. Show an error in ILM explain to indicate there is a problem moving to the next step.

**Steps to reproduce**:

 1. Decrease the poll interval and up the logging.

    ```
    PUT /_cluster/settings
    {
      "persistent": {
        "indices.lifecycle.poll_interval": "1s",
        "logger.org.elasticsearch.xpack.ilm": "TRACE"
      }
    }
    ```

 1. Add an index template

    ```
    PUT /_template/devtest
    {
      "index_patterns": [
        "devtest-*"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "index": {
          "lifecycle": {
            "name": "devtest",
            "rollover_alias": "devtest"
          },
          "number_of_shards": "1",
          "number_of_replicas": "0"
        }
      }
    }
    ```

 1. Add policy version 1. Note the rollover action in the hot phase. 

    ```
    PUT /_ilm/policy/devtest
    {
      "policy": {
        "phases": {
          "hot": {
            "min_age": "0ms",
            "actions": {
              "rollover": {
                "max_size": "50mb",
                "max_age": "2m"
              }
            }
          },
          "delete": {
            "min_age": "2m",
            "actions": {
              "delete": {}
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
    ```

1. Create the index

    ```
    PUT /devtest-000001
    {
      "aliases": {
        "devtest": {
          "is_write_index": true
        }
      }
    }
    ```

1. Let ILM perform an index rollover.

1. Create version 2 of the policy by removing the rollover action from the hot phase. The intention here is to let ILM perform index deletions per policy and prevent creation of a new index.

    ```
    PUT /_ilm/policy/devtest
    {
      "policy": {
        "phases": {
          "hot": {
            "min_age": "0ms",
            "actions": {}
          },
          "delete": {
            "min_age": "2m",
            "actions": {
              "delete": {}
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
    ```

1. Wait a few minutes and observe the last index is stuck in the rollover action of the hot phase.

